docs.abstract: The social media site, a haven for neo-Nazis and other extremists, has lost support from service providers like GoDaddy and PayPal since Saturday’s massacre.
docs.snippet: The social media site, a haven for neo-Nazis and other extremists, has lost support from service providers like GoDaddy and PayPal since Saturday’s massacre.
docs.lead_paragraph: Early Saturday, moments before the police say he barged into a Pittsburgh synagogue and opened fire, Robert Bowers’s anti-Semitic rage finally boiled over as he posted one last message online.

headline.main: On Gab, an Extremist-Friendly Site, Pittsburgh Shooting Suspect Aired His Hatred in Full
headline.print_headline: Social Site Let Suspect’s Hate Spill Unbridled

docs.abstract: The Education Department has significantly mismanaged a debt relief program for public workers, according to a government audit.
docs.snippet: The Education Department has significantly mismanaged a debt relief program for public workers, according to a government audit.
docs.lead_paragraph: A program intended to wipe away the student loans of qualifying public servants has rejected more than 99 percent of those who applied, according to a government audit that found that “fragmented” management and “piecemeal” operating instructions had contributed to the failure to forgive more debt.

headline.main: 28,000 Public Servants Sought Student Loan Forgiveness. 96 Got It.
headline.print_headline: 28,000 Public Servants Sought Student Loan Forgiveness. 96 Received It.

docs.abstract: The deal, worth $15 billion, ends Rupert Murdoch’s connection with Sky, and provides money for Disney to invest in streaming.
docs.snippet: The deal, worth $15 billion, ends Rupert Murdoch’s connection with Sky, and provides money for Disney to invest in streaming.
docs.lead_paragraph: Twenty-First Century Fox agreed to sell its 39 percent stake in the British broadcaster Sky to Comcast on Wednesday in a deal worth $15 billion, ending Rupert Murdoch’s yearslong ambition to take full ownership of the satellite service he helped found three decades ago.

headline.main: Fox, Acting on Behalf of Disney, Sells Its Stake in Sky to Comcast
headline.print_headline: Fox, Acting on Disney’s Behalf, Sells Stake in Sky to Comcast at a High Price

byline.original: By Edmund Lee and Brooks Barnes

docs.abstract: American companies are turning to students to push products on their personal social media accounts.
docs.snippet: American companies are turning to students to push products on their personal social media accounts.
docs.lead_paragraph: Noah Lamfers, a senior at the University of Northern Iowa, had never tried a 5-Hour Energy drink. But he still signed up to promote the brand online, getting paid to post images of himself and bottles of the product on his personal Facebook, Instagram and Snapchat accounts. He tagged each one with #5houruintern.

headline.main: The Hot College Gig: Online Brand Promoter

docs.abstract: The S.E.C. said that Renaud Laplanche had improperly approved alterations to some of the company’s lending products to bolster the company’s financial performance.

docs.lead_paragraph: San Francisco — Renaud Laplanche, a leading figure in Silicon Valley’s effort to challenge the financial industry, reached a settlement with federal regulators on Friday over accusations that he had fraudulently inflated his company’s returns.

docs.abstract: The ride-hailing company faced charges that it covered up a breach of user data, rather than immediately notifying consumers.
docs.snippet: The ride-hailing company faced charges that it covered up a breach of user data, rather than immediately notifying consumers.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Uber will pay $148 million to settle a nationwide investigation into a 2016 data breach, in which a hacker managed to gain access to information belonging to 57 million riders and drivers. The breach included names and driver’s license numbers for 600,000 drivers.

headline.main: Uber Settles Data Breach Investigation for $148 Million
headline.print_headline: Uber to Pay $148 Million Over Data Breach
